    {
      "id": "c4536506bb9eab37192160086a3d1e9b53b81159",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-28 23:33:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI like the addition to contrib/, but I'm not a fan of the make target.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "842c49701f727d9ad6f9a2fea538032efcb1992c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-06-29 05:59:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIMHO, the point of having a \"make\" target is for ease of use for the developer, regardless of whether it is part of the \"packaging\" or not. In the end, that is what make is all about - simplifying repetitive tasks. It's not like the commands required for checking this are easy to use or remember...\n\nIf you are worried about two lines of cruft, I could add a comment that makes it clear that this is now four lines of cruft to be removed in the late 2.5 or early 2.6 timeframe (depending when all of the cfs_ wrappers have been removed).  The sed script itself will need to be removed as well.\n\nWhile I do appreciate your interest to improve the build system, in the end I don't think these two lines seriously add complexity to the build system.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
